WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.303 --> 00:00:15.931
MACE: You refer to the prophecy of the
one who will bring balance to the Force.

2
00:00:17.433 --> 00:00:19.184
You believe it's this boy?

3
00:00:23.397 --> 00:00:26.650
Anakin Skywalker. meet Obi-Wan Kenobi.

4
00:00:28.444 --> 00:00:31.280
YODA: Clouded this boy's future is.

5
00:00:33.032 --> 00:00:36.410
The boy is dangerous.
They all sense it. Why can't you?

6
00:00:37.036 --> 00:00:39.621
An apprentice you have. Qui-Gon.

7
00:00:39.705 --> 00:00:41.915
Impossible to take on a second.

8
00:00:41.999 --> 00:00:44.459
-Obi-Wan is ready.
-I am ready to face the trials.

9
00:00:50.299 --> 00:00:52.050
QUI-GON: You've been a good apprentice.
Obi-Wan.

10
00:00:54.512 --> 00:00:56.222
No!

11
00:00:57.223 --> 00:00:59.350
QUI-GON: [ foresee you will become
a great Jedi Knight.

12
00:00:59.433 --> 00:01:00.892
Obi-Wan.

13
00:01:00.977 --> 00:01:02.979
Promise me you will train the boy.

14
00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:04.564
Yes. Master.

15
00:01:04.647 --> 00:01:08.067
He will bring balance.

16
00:01:08.484 --> 00:01:11.612
Master Yoda. I gave Qui-Gon my word.

17
00:01:12.280 --> 00:01:15.074
YODA: Your apprentice Skywalker will be.

18
00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:20.621
What took you so long?

19
00:01:23.666 --> 00:01:25.334
ANAKIN: Obi-Wan is a great mentor.

20
00:01:26.294 --> 00:01:27.586
As wise as Master Yoda

21
00:01:29.046 --> 00:01:30.964
and as powerful as Master Windu.

22
00:01:31.591 --> 00:01:33.884
PALPATINE: You are the most gifted Jedi
I have ever met.

23
00:01:35.553 --> 00:01:38.430
I see you becoming
the greatest of all the Jedi.

24
00:01:39.765 --> 00:01:40.807
ANAKIN: / feel lost.

25
00:01:41.934 --> 00:01:44.811
Lost? What do you mean?

26
00:01:44.895 --> 00:01:47.522
ANAKIN: I'm not the Jedi I should be.
I want more.

27
00:01:48.190 --> 00:01:49.191
And I know I shouldn't.

28
00:01:50.151 --> 00:01:51.902
How do you know the ways of the Force?

29
00:01:52.987 --> 00:01:55.656
My mentor taught me everything
about the Force.

30
00:01:56.699 --> 00:01:59.410
Even the nature of the dark side

31
00:02:01.037 --> 00:02:02.621
Only through me

32
00:02:02.705 --> 00:02:06.333
can you achieve a power
greater than any Jed..

33
00:02:06.542 --> 00:02:08.252
(GASPING) I can't.

34
00:02:08.711 --> 00:02:09.837
Don't give up. Padmé.

35
00:02:11.297 --> 00:02:13.465
<i>PALPATINE: The power to save Padmé.</i>

36
00:02:14.216 --> 00:02:16.301
ANAKIN: I found a way to save you.

37
00:02:16.385 --> 00:02:20.885
YODA: Twisted by the dark side
young Skywalker has become.

38
00:02:23.017 --> 00:02:25.853
The boy you trained. gone he is.

39
00:02:25.936 --> 00:02:27.395
I will not kill Anakin.

40
00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:32.108
This is the end for you. my master.

41
00:02:32.735 --> 00:02:34.111
I have failed you. Anakin.

42
00:02:35.071 --> 00:02:36.072
I have failed you.

43
00:02:37.865 --> 00:02:40.868
It's over. Anakin.
I have the high ground.

44
00:02:40.951 --> 00:02:43.620
You underestimate my power.

45
00:02:43.871 --> 00:02:45.372
(ANAKIN SCREAMING)

46
00:02:46.624 --> 00:02:48.375
You were the Chosen One!

47
00:02:48.459 --> 00:02:51.336
It was said that you would
destroy the Sith. not join them!

48
00:02:54.298 --> 00:02:55.841
He's still alive.

49
00:03:01.222 --> 00:03:03.015
OBI-WAN: You were my brother. Anakin.

50
00:03:05.351 --> 00:03:09.851
PALPATINE: You shall be known
as Darth Vader.

51
00:03:11.357 --> 00:03:12.441
PADME: Obi-Wan?

52
00:03:13.234 --> 00:03:15.027
There's good in him.
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

53
00:03:17.154 --> 00:03:18.238
PALPATINE: Rise.

54
00:03:21.117 --> 00:03:24.703
YODA: Hidden.
safe the children must be kept.

55
00:03:27.456 --> 00:03:28.790
OBI-WAN: We must take them somewhere

56
00:03:28.874 --> 00:03:30.917
where the Sith
will not sense their presence.

57
00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:34.004
My wife and I will take the girl.

58
00:03:34.714 --> 00:03:37.133
We've always talked
of adopting a baby girl.

59
00:03:37.925 --> 00:03:38.926
PADME: Leia.

60
00:03:39.009 --> 00:03:40.010
And what of the boy?

61
00:03:40.428 --> 00:03:41.429
PADME: Luke.

62
00:03:41.595 --> 00:03:44.222
To Tatooine. To his family send him.

63
00:03:44.306 --> 00:03:46.266
I will take the child
and watch over him.

64
00:03:48.310 --> 00:03:49.561
YODA: In your solitude...

65
00:03:50.271 --> 00:03:52.106
training I have for you.

66
00:03:52.189 --> 00:03:54.149
Your old master.

67
00:03:54.692 --> 00:03:57.778
How to commune with him
I will teach you.

68
00:04:50.331 --> 00:04:51.332
(WHOOSHING)

69
00:04:52.166 --> 00:04:53.500
(ALL GASPING)

70
00:04:54.668 --> 00:04:56.169
FEMALE YOUNGLING 1: This way! Quick!

71
00:04:56.587 --> 00:05:00.632
-(CLONE TROOPER GRUNTS)
-(VELTI GRUNTS)

72
00:05:01.383 --> 00:05:02.384
Come on! Let's go!

73
00:05:02.468 --> 00:05:04.720
MALE YOUNGLING: Let's go!
FEMALE YOUNGLING 1: This way!

74
00:05:07.389 --> 00:05:08.390
Come on! Let's go!

75
00:05:08.474 --> 00:05:10.809
FEMALE YOUNGLING 1: This way.
FEMALE YOUNGLING 2: Hurry!

76
00:05:10.935 --> 00:05:12.436
(VELTI GRUNTING)

77
00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:13.979
FEMALE YOUNGLING 1: Watch out!

78
00:05:15.481 --> 00:05:16.982
(CLONE TROOPER SCREAMS)

79
00:05:17.316 --> 00:05:19.067
Come on! Move! Quick!

80
00:05:19.443 --> 00:05:22.446
(VELTI GRUNTING)

81
00:05:23.614 --> 00:05:26.325
-Go. Come on! Go. Go! Go!
-Run! This way! Hurry!

82
00:05:27.326 --> 00:05:29.828
(GRUNTING CONTINUES)

83
00:05:34.416 --> 00:05:36.418
(VELTI GROANING)

84
00:05:36.544 --> 00:05:37.711
FEMALE YOUNGLING 1: No!

85
00:05:38.337 --> 00:05:41.590
-(BLASTERS FIRING IN DISTANCE)
-(JEDIS GRUNTING. GROANING)

86
00:05:42.091 --> 00:05:43.092
What do we do now?

87
00:05:43.968 --> 00:05:44.969
We run.

88
00:05:45.094 --> 00:05:48.097
(JEDIS GROANING)

89
00:05:48.222 --> 00:05:51.225
PALPATINE: (ON SPEAKERS)
Execute Order 66.

90
00:05:52.101 --> 00:05:55.270
Execute Order 66.

91
00:05:56.313 --> 00:05:59.733
Execute Order 66.

92
00:06:13.122 --> 00:06:15.124
(WIND WHISTLING)

93
00:06:20.254 --> 00:06:22.547
(INDISTINCT CHATTER IN OTHER LANGUAGES)

94
00:06:31.015 --> 00:06:34.101
(SPACECRAFT WHOOSHING)

95
00:06:34.184 --> 00:06:36.394
(JAWAS SPEAKING JAWAESE)

96
00:07:02.338 --> 00:07:06.091
(ALL MURMURING INDISTINCTLY)

97
00:08:00.688 --> 00:08:02.064
(GROWLS)

98
00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:20.249
(GRAND INQUISITOR CLEARS THROAT)

99
00:08:32.094 --> 00:08:34.763
You know who we are.

100
00:08:35.431 --> 00:08:36.432
Inquisitors.

101
00:08:36.515 --> 00:08:38.475
You know what we do?

102
00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:39.810
You hunt Jedi.

103
00:08:39.893 --> 00:08:44.393
In actuality. I would say
the Jedi hunt themselves.

104
00:08:50.070 --> 00:08:53.990
Do you know the key
to hunting a Jedi. friend?

105
00:08:55.284 --> 00:08:57.119
It is patience.

106
00:09:00.122 --> 00:09:02.624
Jedi cannot help what they are.

107
00:09:04.251 --> 00:09:06.836
Their compassion leaves a trail.

108
00:09:07.713 --> 00:09:12.213
For example.
in our line of work. rumors run rampant.

109
00:09:14.553 --> 00:09:16.555
Here's one I heard just recently.

110
00:09:16.638 --> 00:09:21.138
It involves a Jedi hiding right here
in your lovely saloon.

111
00:09:23.771 --> 00:09:26.732
Let's say ours is a wanderer.

112
00:09:28.025 --> 00:09:30.235
Maybe he's looking for people like him.

113
00:09:31.403 --> 00:09:34.155
Comes across this establishment.

114
00:09:34.239 --> 00:09:35.323
Nice place.

115
00:09:36.825 --> 00:09:40.411
And then he sees you.

116
00:09:42.331 --> 00:09:43.498
A man in need.

117
00:09:46.085 --> 00:09:48.337
Perhaps the locals
are stealing from you.

118
00:09:49.755 --> 00:09:51.047
Threatening you.

119
00:09:51.632 --> 00:09:54.384
So what is the Jedi to do?

120
00:09:57.304 --> 00:10:00.765
Help you and risk exposure?

121
00:10:02.851 --> 00:10:03.935
Or move on?

122
00:10:05.145 --> 00:10:09.645
Now. if he were smart. he'd keep moving.
but the Jedi Code is like an itch.

123
00:10:10.526 --> 00:10:12.361
He cannot help it.

124
00:10:12.444 --> 00:10:15.822
So he steps in and saves your saloon.

125
00:10:15.906 --> 00:10:18.450
You offer him a place to hide.

126
00:10:18.534 --> 00:10:20.911
Fresh water. shade from the suns.

127
00:10:20.994 --> 00:10:25.164
but the stories. they begin
and they travel quickly.

128
00:10:25.249 --> 00:10:28.293
His compassion has been his undoing.

129
00:10:28.627 --> 00:10:30.128
-(GRUNTS)
-(GASPS)

130
00:10:35.008 --> 00:10:36.092
REVA: There.

131
00:10:36.218 --> 00:10:38.595
-(NARI GRUNTING)
-(PEOPLE GASPING)

132
00:10:38.679 --> 00:10:41.598
-(GROWLS)
(GRUNTING)

133
00:10:41.682 --> 00:10:43.475
(CROWD GASPING)

134
00:10:43.559 --> 00:10:45.060
Prepare him for interrogation.

135
00:10:45.144 --> 00:10:47.604
You're wasting your time.
You know that. right?

136
00:10:48.480 --> 00:10:49.606
You'll never find us all.

137
00:10:49.982 --> 00:10:52.526
-(GRUNTING)
-(GROANING)

138
00:10:53.610 --> 00:10:56.362
-(GROANS)
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

139
00:10:56.446 --> 00:10:58.781
-(GRUNTS)
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)

140
00:10:58.866 --> 00:11:02.411
(CROWD MUTTERING)

141
00:11:04.163 --> 00:11:05.831
GRAND INQUISITOR: You are reckless.

142
00:11:07.124 --> 00:11:08.291
Why chase after scraps?

143
00:11:08.375 --> 00:11:10.710
Scraps are all we have left.

144
00:11:10.794 --> 00:11:12.420
Then we should be hunting bigger prey.

145
00:11:12.504 --> 00:11:15.632
He is not yours to find.
We are past this. Third Sister.

146
00:11:15.716 --> 00:11:17.592
I will not warn you again.

147
00:11:17.676 --> 00:11:19.928
You will forget this fixation
with Kenobi.

148
00:11:20.012 --> 00:11:22.139
or I will relieve you of your duties.

149
00:11:22.222 --> 00:11:23.306
Is that clear?

150
00:11:25.559 --> 00:11:27.769
Yes. Grand Inquisitor.

151
00:11:33.609 --> 00:11:35.235
(SOFTLY) Consider him forgotten.

152
00:11:58.258 --> 00:12:02.178
(WIND WHOOSHING)

153
00:12:08.894 --> 00:12:10.937
(WORKERS CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

154
00:12:11.355 --> 00:12:15.609
(PANTING)

155
00:12:15.692 --> 00:12:16.776
(GRUNTS)

156
00:12:16.860 --> 00:12:20.280
(FOREMEN SHOUTING ORDERS)

157
00:12:20.781 --> 00:12:23.784
(INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES)

158
00:12:32.918 --> 00:12:35.003
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

159
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:40.008
(DROID SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

160
00:13:12.624 --> 00:13:13.875
It's only half.

161
00:13:16.753 --> 00:13:17.754
Please. I have a family.

162
00:13:17.838 --> 00:13:18.839
(GROANS)

163
00:13:19.923 --> 00:13:21.633
One more word. I take it all.

164
00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.304
Keep moving.

165
00:13:31.935 --> 00:13:33.269
Something you want to say?

166
00:13:41.111 --> 00:13:43.279
-(MACHINE DINGS)
-(COINS CLINKING)

167
00:13:46.533 --> 00:13:48.117
(SCOFFS)

168
00:13:49.536 --> 00:13:52.497
(FOREMAN SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)

169
00:13:58.545 --> 00:14:00.547
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

170
00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:03.841
(WORKERS SIGHING WEARILY)

171
00:14:25.238 --> 00:14:26.656
(EOPIE GRUNTS)

172
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:35.207
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

173
00:15:27.843 --> 00:15:30.053
(WHIRRING)

174
00:15:30.470 --> 00:15:31.554
(BEEPS)

175
00:16:06.047 --> 00:16:09.175
(WHIRRING)

176
00:16:09.718 --> 00:16:11.177
(IN JAWAESE) Should have brought
some soap.

177
00:16:12.637 --> 00:16:14.597
I could smell you from Anchorhead.

178
00:16:15.849 --> 00:16:17.183
OBI-WAN: (IN ENGLISH) You're late.

179
00:16:17.267 --> 00:16:19.143
Do you have the credits this time?

180
00:16:19.227 --> 00:16:20.394
Do you have it?

181
00:16:22.522 --> 00:16:23.606
A hundred.

182
00:16:26.276 --> 00:16:27.485
It's very rare.

183
00:16:28.111 --> 00:16:29.821
They don't make these anymore.

184
00:16:29.905 --> 00:16:31.323
I'll give you...

185
00:16:32.240 --> 00:16:33.449
I'll give you 50.

186
00:16:33.992 --> 00:16:35.076
Seventy five.

187
00:16:35.285 --> 00:16:36.911
I've got a tribe to feed.

188
00:16:37.287 --> 00:16:39.622
(VAPORATOR SPUTTERING)

189
00:16:39.915 --> 00:16:41.917
Trouble with your vapor at or?

190
00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:44.836
Yes. I had some parts stolen.
I need a new processor board.

191
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:46.504
(EXCLAIMING)

192
00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:49.382
You're in luck.

193
00:16:51.134 --> 00:16:54.470
Teeka. if you're gonna steal my parts
and then sell them back to me.

194
00:16:54.554 --> 00:16:57.431
could you at least clean them first
as a courtesy?

195
00:16:57.933 --> 00:16:59.976
Cleaning costs extra.

196
00:17:06.608 --> 00:17:08.067
You need anything else?

197
00:17:08.902 --> 00:17:11.529
I have a whole new batch of salvage.

198
00:17:12.239 --> 00:17:13.490
Here. look...

199
00:17:13.698 --> 00:17:15.991
We stripped that Jedi's old ship.

200
00:17:16.493 --> 00:17:19.871
Found it out in the wastes.

201
00:17:21.414 --> 00:17:22.415
A Jedi?

202
00:17:22.499 --> 00:17:24.501
One escaped across the Dune Sea.

203
00:17:24.834 --> 00:17:26.335
Inquisitors and everything.

204
00:17:27.879 --> 00:17:29.088
Hope we get more of them.

205
00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.507
Good for business...

206
00:17:31.925 --> 00:17:33.593
(SCOFFS) Well. don't count on it.

207
00:17:34.594 --> 00:17:36.971
I've heard the Jedi are all but extinct.

208
00:17:39.140 --> 00:17:40.224
Here.

209
00:17:41.560 --> 00:17:43.728
You know. you really do stink.

210
00:17:45.605 --> 00:17:47.231
Well. thank you. Teeka. Goodbye.

211
00:17:48.817 --> 00:17:49.859
(TEEKA GRUNTS)

212
00:17:50.277 --> 00:17:52.779
(WHIRRING)

213
00:18:02.122 --> 00:18:03.456
PADME: I know there's...

214
00:18:06.293 --> 00:18:07.669
OBI-WAN: You were my brother. Anakin!

215
00:18:08.461 --> 00:18:10.004
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

216
00:18:10.630 --> 00:18:12.673
-Promise me you will train the boy.
-(LAUGHING)

217
00:18:14.217 --> 00:18:15.259
PADME: Obi-Wan...

218
00:18:16.011 --> 00:18:18.430
-YODA: Only pain will you find.
-(QUINN GRUNTS)

219
00:18:19.139 --> 00:18:21.307
PADME: There's good in him.
I know there's...

220
00:18:22.183 --> 00:18:23.475
OBI-WAN: You were the Chosen One!

221
00:18:23.560 --> 00:18:25.478
(BABY WAILING)

222
00:18:25.562 --> 00:18:26.729
I hate you!

223
00:18:27.731 --> 00:18:29.607
-(PADME SCREAMS)
-(WHOOSHING)

224
00:18:29.691 --> 00:18:30.733
(INHALES SHARPLY)

225
00:18:30.817 --> 00:18:32.151
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

226
00:18:37.741 --> 00:18:40.702
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

227
00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:46.165
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

228
00:18:48.543 --> 00:18:49.627
Master Qui-Gon.

229
00:18:53.840 --> 00:18:54.924
Master?

230
00:18:59.971 --> 00:19:03.265
(SIGHING)

231
00:19:06.394 --> 00:19:08.270
(CHITTERING)

232
00:19:14.444 --> 00:19:16.446
(EOPIE BELLOWING)

233
00:19:39.511 --> 00:19:40.970
(EOPIE GRUNTS)

234
00:19:48.019 --> 00:19:50.688
OWEN: Grab two of those canisters.

235
00:19:50.897 --> 00:19:52.189
(WHIRRING)

236
00:20:03.910 --> 00:20:04.994
Luke?

237
00:20:07.247 --> 00:20:08.373
(WHIRS)

238
00:20:09.958 --> 00:20:11.042
Luke!

239
00:20:11.876 --> 00:20:12.877
Luke!

240
00:20:12.961 --> 00:20:14.796
Did he go back inside?

241
00:20:14.879 --> 00:20:15.963
He's run off.

242
00:20:18.007 --> 00:20:19.091
Luke?

243
00:20:24.931 --> 00:20:26.015
BERU: Luke?

244
00:20:30.979 --> 00:20:32.063
OWEN: Luke?

245
00:20:35.108 --> 00:20:37.985
-(PLAYFUL CHATTER)
-(BERU LAUGHS)

246
00:21:15.398 --> 00:21:18.567
(EOPIE GRUNTING)

247
00:21:23.114 --> 00:21:25.574
(RUSTLING)

248
00:21:35.001 --> 00:21:38.045
(SMALL ROCKS FALLING)

249
00:21:41.466 --> 00:21:42.550
MAN: Master.

250
00:21:43.968 --> 00:21:46.220
I thought I saw you in the town.
but I wasn't sure.

251
00:21:46.304 --> 00:21:47.847
I didn't think you'd survived.

252
00:21:47.931 --> 00:21:49.933
You're making some kind of mistake.

253
00:21:50.016 --> 00:21:51.559
I'm sorry. my name is NARI.

254
00:21:52.477 --> 00:21:53.519
Um. there's no mistake.

255
00:21:55.146 --> 00:21:56.856
You're looking for somebody else.

256
00:21:58.107 --> 00:21:59.525
What are you doing here. Obi-Wan?

257
00:21:59.609 --> 00:22:00.735
My name is Ben.

258
00:22:01.569 --> 00:22:02.653
NARI: Come on. please.

259
00:22:03.154 --> 00:22:04.238
Please.

260
00:22:05.824 --> 00:22:07.659
You have no idea what I've been through.

261
00:22:21.339 --> 00:22:22.506
You must leave.

262
00:22:23.424 --> 00:22:24.716
You'll draw too much attention.

263
00:22:24.801 --> 00:22:26.093
But I have nowhere to go.

264
00:22:26.177 --> 00:22:28.554
They're hunting me. You have to help me.

265
00:22:30.098 --> 00:22:31.182
You want my help?

266
00:22:31.641 --> 00:22:32.725
Take this.

267
00:22:33.226 --> 00:22:36.062
Walk into the middle of the desert
and bury it in the ground.

268
00:22:38.773 --> 00:22:39.774
Stay hidden.

269
00:22:41.568 --> 00:22:42.569
Live a normal life.

270
00:22:42.652 --> 00:22:45.488
What about the people that need us?
What about the fight?

271
00:22:46.823 --> 00:22:47.990
The fight is done.

272
00:22:48.867 --> 00:22:49.951
We lost.

273
00:22:52.412 --> 00:22:53.496
What happened to you?

274
00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:57.041
You were once a great Jedi.

275
00:23:00.128 --> 00:23:02.213
The time of the Jedi is over.

276
00:23:07.677 --> 00:23:08.969
Go back to the town.

277
00:23:10.179 --> 00:23:11.263
Let it go.

278
00:23:56.643 --> 00:23:58.102
We're going to be late.

279
00:23:58.186 --> 00:24:00.062
Come on. let's hurry it along.

280
00:24:00.146 --> 00:24:01.147
How is she doing?

281
00:24:01.230 --> 00:24:02.231
She's ready?

282
00:24:02.815 --> 00:24:03.899
Great.

283
00:24:04.525 --> 00:24:05.776
Thank you.

284
00:24:05.860 --> 00:24:08.320
Remember.
my sister's whole family is coming.

285
00:24:08.821 --> 00:24:10.113
We need their support.

286
00:24:10.198 --> 00:24:11.782
So try not to make anyone cry.

287
00:24:11.866 --> 00:24:14.326
There will be sweetmallows
at the reception after.

288
00:24:15.036 --> 00:24:17.455
If you behave. I will let you...

289
00:24:23.336 --> 00:24:26.130
She insisted you would find it amusing.
Your Highness.

290
00:24:31.219 --> 00:24:33.471
She's either in the cellar.
in the kitchen...

291
00:24:34.305 --> 00:24:36.015
(SIGHS) ...or in the woods.

292
00:24:41.854 --> 00:24:43.313
(DROID CHIRPING)

293
00:25:12.844 --> 00:25:14.595
(CHIRPING)

294
00:25:14.721 --> 00:25:16.889
(SPACECRAFT WHIRRING)

295
00:25:17.056 --> 00:25:18.474
Medical freighter.

296
00:25:19.976 --> 00:25:21.852
Pleasure barge. boring.

297
00:25:21.936 --> 00:25:23.062
(SAD CHIRP)

298
00:25:23.604 --> 00:25:25.606
Casino ship? Not bad.

299
00:25:25.690 --> 00:25:26.774
(CHIRPS IN AGREEMENT)

300
00:25:27.942 --> 00:25:29.944
Ooh. A Tri-wing. That's a new one.

301
00:25:30.028 --> 00:25:31.237
(CHIRPS EXCITEDLY)

302
00:25:31.320 --> 00:25:33.155
Ooh. An Aquillian Ranger.

303
00:25:33.239 --> 00:25:36.617
Probably scouting for Merson pirates.

304
00:25:36.701 --> 00:25:38.202
(CHIRPS)

305
00:25:38.286 --> 00:25:40.288
No? Trader. maybe?

306
00:25:40.371 --> 00:25:41.538
BREHA: Leia Organa!

307
00:25:43.416 --> 00:25:45.167
You had to do this today?

308
00:25:45.251 --> 00:25:46.252
Do what?

309
00:25:46.335 --> 00:25:47.419
Down.

310
00:25:48.004 --> 00:25:49.505
(CHIRPS NERVOUSLY)

311
00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:54.343
It is like raising a Glor-ag.

312
00:26:00.266 --> 00:26:01.600
No Lola for the rest of the day.

313
00:26:01.684 --> 00:26:03.727
But she didn't do anything.

314
00:26:03.811 --> 00:26:04.812
Shut her down.

315
00:26:06.355 --> 00:26:07.439
I mean it.

316
00:26:09.484 --> 00:26:11.360
(LOLA DEACTIVATES)

317
00:26:14.072 --> 00:26:17.033
If you behaved as well as you climb.

318
00:26:17.575 --> 00:26:19.201
you'd be a senator already.

319
00:26:19.702 --> 00:26:21.161
(SIGHS)

320
00:26:21.245 --> 00:26:23.705
(SIGHS) You'll have to change
in the speeder. Come.

321
00:26:23.790 --> 00:26:27.210
It's not like anyone would miss me
if I wasn't there.

322
00:26:27.293 --> 00:26:28.377
I'd miss you.

323
00:26:28.461 --> 00:26:30.212
All I ever do is wave.

324
00:26:30.296 --> 00:26:31.880
BREHA: Then do more than wave.

325
00:26:31.964 --> 00:26:34.091
You get out of this
what you put into it.

326
00:26:35.843 --> 00:26:37.010
LEIA: I'm sorry. Mother.

327
00:26:37.678 --> 00:26:39.012
I really am.

328
00:26:39.597 --> 00:26:41.890
I promise I won't do it again.

329
00:26:45.019 --> 00:26:46.437
(SIGHS)

330
00:26:47.814 --> 00:26:50.566
You know. I can feel you doing that.

331
00:26:51.275 --> 00:26:52.276
Come on.

332
00:26:52.360 --> 00:26:54.278
LEIA: It's like living in a prison.

333
00:26:54.362 --> 00:26:55.446
BREHA: A prison?

334
00:26:56.656 --> 00:26:59.659
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

335
00:27:02.203 --> 00:27:06.248
-(WHISTLE BLOWING)
-(WORKERS CHATTERING WEARILY)

336
00:27:32.316 --> 00:27:35.944
(WHOOSHING)

337
00:27:40.324 --> 00:27:43.493
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

338
00:27:50.501 --> 00:27:51.710
(CLATTERS)

339
00:27:53.963 --> 00:27:55.631
I want you to stay away from him.

340
00:27:56.924 --> 00:27:58.717
We don't need anything from you. Ben.

341
00:27:58.801 --> 00:28:00.385
It's just a toy.

342
00:28:00.469 --> 00:28:02.012
It's a lot more than that.

343
00:28:02.096 --> 00:28:04.890
There's more to life
than your farm. Owen.

344
00:28:04.974 --> 00:28:07.893
He needs to see that.
There's a whole galaxy out there.

345
00:28:07.977 --> 00:28:11.271
I'm asking you to leave us alone. Ben.

346
00:28:11.355 --> 00:28:12.356
I mean it.

347
00:28:12.857 --> 00:28:13.858
Is he okay?

348
00:28:15.193 --> 00:28:17.069
You don't care if he's okay.

349
00:28:18.362 --> 00:28:19.696
You care if he's showing.

350
00:28:19.780 --> 00:28:21.490
He's my responsibility. Owen.

351
00:28:21.574 --> 00:28:23.242
-I'm his uncle.
-We talked about this.

352
00:28:23.326 --> 00:28:25.745
When the time comes. he must be trained.

353
00:28:25.828 --> 00:28:27.204
Like you trained his father?

354
00:28:28.789 --> 00:28:30.874
Anakin is dead. Ben.

355
00:28:32.460 --> 00:28:34.879
and I won't let you
make the same mistake twice.

356
00:28:36.214 --> 00:28:39.884
So. leave him on the farm
with his family. where he belongs.

357
00:28:42.511 --> 00:28:44.513
MAN: Move. Now.

358
00:28:44.972 --> 00:28:46.890
-(CROWD MURMURING)
-Get back.

359
00:28:48.059 --> 00:28:49.143
All of you.

360
00:28:50.686 --> 00:28:51.770
Out of the way.

361
00:28:55.358 --> 00:28:56.525
Back up.

362
00:29:02.198 --> 00:29:04.033
You know why we are here.

363
00:29:05.868 --> 00:29:10.038
There is a Jedi hiding on this planet.

364
00:29:10.122 --> 00:29:12.666
We need to know where he is.

365
00:29:14.043 --> 00:29:15.502
You will be rewarded well.

366
00:29:15.586 --> 00:29:16.628
Or you'll be punished!

367
00:29:16.712 --> 00:29:17.754
FIFTH BROTHER: Reva!

368
00:29:17.838 --> 00:29:19.381
Hands go first!

369
00:29:21.676 --> 00:29:24.345
That way. when you reach for anything.

370
00:29:26.973 --> 00:29:28.057
you think of us.

371
00:29:33.562 --> 00:29:35.146
WOMAN: This is the Outer Rim.

372
00:29:36.399 --> 00:29:37.983
You have no rights here.

373
00:29:38.526 --> 00:29:40.319
We're not under the Empire's...

374
00:29:40.403 --> 00:29:43.072
-(WOMAN SCREAMING)
-(CROWD GASPING. EXCLAIMING)

375
00:29:43.155 --> 00:29:45.198
REVA: All we want is information.

376
00:29:45.950 --> 00:29:50.450
If anyone knows anything about a Jedi...

377
00:29:57.169 --> 00:29:58.336
You know something?

378
00:30:06.178 --> 00:30:07.262
What's your name?

379
00:30:08.514 --> 00:30:09.640
Owen.

380
00:30:10.599 --> 00:30:11.683
REVA: Owen.

381
00:30:12.101 --> 00:30:13.435
Farmer. right?

382
00:30:14.854 --> 00:30:15.855
Wife?

383
00:30:15.938 --> 00:30:16.939
Kids?

384
00:30:18.357 --> 00:30:19.775
My family's of no concern to you.

385
00:30:19.859 --> 00:30:21.151
They might be.

386
00:30:21.235 --> 00:30:23.862
-You got a Jedi on that farm. too?
-No.

387
00:30:23.946 --> 00:30:25.197
Why should I believe you?

388
00:30:25.281 --> 00:30:27.074
I have no love for the Jedi.

389
00:30:28.200 --> 00:30:29.284
Jedi are vermin.

390
00:30:30.453 --> 00:30:32.163
I kill vermin on my farm.

391
00:30:33.164 --> 00:30:34.665
You protect your family.

392
00:30:37.376 --> 00:30:38.627
I like that. Owen.

393
00:30:41.464 --> 00:30:42.465
It's important.

394
00:30:49.764 --> 00:30:51.849
You think
you could protect them from me?

395
00:30:53.601 --> 00:30:54.768
(SCOFFS)

396
00:30:55.811 --> 00:31:00.311
(SHOUTING) Tell me where the Jedi is.
or this man and his family die!

397
00:31:01.317 --> 00:31:03.235
(CROWD GASPING)

398
00:31:04.236 --> 00:31:05.737
The Jedi are cowards.

399
00:31:07.823 --> 00:31:09.658
They failed you.

400
00:31:09.742 --> 00:31:12.494
abandoned you.

401
00:31:13.120 --> 00:31:15.789
There is no point in protecting them.

402
00:31:15.873 --> 00:31:17.916
They would not do the same for you.

403
00:31:22.505 --> 00:31:24.048
But you can save this man.

404
00:31:30.554 --> 00:31:32.180
-Save his family.
-(LIGHTSABER ACTIVATES)

405
00:31:32.264 --> 00:31:34.599
(CROWD GASPING)

406
00:31:38.479 --> 00:31:39.605
FIFTH BROTHER: Enough!

407
00:31:41.357 --> 00:31:43.192
If you remember anything.

408
00:31:43.734 --> 00:31:45.318
rewards will be given.

409
00:31:47.822 --> 00:31:49.824
Stand down. Third Sister.

410
00:31:52.076 --> 00:31:53.160
Now!

411
00:31:54.328 --> 00:31:55.537
(LIGHTSABER DEACTIVATES)

412
00:31:55.621 --> 00:31:57.039
Next time. Owen.

413
00:32:00.126 --> 00:32:03.379
(CROWD MURMURING)

414
00:32:03.462 --> 00:32:05.046
FIFTH BROTHER: Ah! Move.

415
00:32:05.881 --> 00:32:09.676
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

416
00:32:12.471 --> 00:32:13.638
(BOTH GRUNT)

417
00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:17.101
You are too impulsive.

418
00:32:17.685 --> 00:32:19.186
I'm sick of wasting time!

419
00:32:19.937 --> 00:32:21.605
This place is beneath us!

420
00:32:22.189 --> 00:32:23.940
The Grand Inquisitor was right.

421
00:32:25.484 --> 00:32:27.027
You still want Kenobi.

422
00:32:28.904 --> 00:32:32.032
But he's gone. and you won't find him.

423
00:32:32.825 --> 00:32:35.410
We spent the last ten years
looking for him.

424
00:32:37.079 --> 00:32:39.414
Maybe you've been looking
in the wrong places.

425
00:32:40.291 --> 00:32:43.711
What is it you think you will gain
by capturing him?

426
00:32:45.087 --> 00:32:46.296
What I'm owed.

427
00:32:51.635 --> 00:32:53.553
Be careful. Third Sister.

428
00:32:53.637 --> 00:32:55.388
You go too far.

429
00:32:57.266 --> 00:32:59.017
Maybe you don't go far enough.

430
00:33:02.396 --> 00:33:05.399
-(WHOOSHING)
(CROWD MURMURING)

431
00:33:10.070 --> 00:33:11.112
Thank you. Owen.

432
00:33:11.572 --> 00:33:12.698
(SCOFFS)

433
00:33:17.411 --> 00:33:18.870
I didn't do it for you.

434
00:33:29.715 --> 00:33:32.217
(WHOOSHING)

435
00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:58.035
Right on time as always.

436
00:33:58.118 --> 00:33:59.452
Anything good today?

437
00:33:59.537 --> 00:34:01.997
A trade ship and an Aquillian Ranger.

438
00:34:02.081 --> 00:34:03.832
Probably scouring for pirates.

439
00:34:03.916 --> 00:34:05.459
That's what I said.

440
00:34:05.543 --> 00:34:07.419
-Don't encourage her.
-All right.

441
00:34:10.714 --> 00:34:11.923
Come now.

442
00:34:12.007 --> 00:34:13.633
Let's get this over with.

443
00:34:16.804 --> 00:34:18.847
(LIVELY CHATTER)

444
00:34:18.931 --> 00:34:20.098
-Breha.
-Sister.

445
00:34:20.182 --> 00:34:21.433
-BAIL: Greetings.
-LEIA: Hi. cousin.

446
00:34:26.397 --> 00:34:27.439
MAN: Princess.

447
00:34:27.523 --> 00:34:29.858
-WOMAN: Oh. there they are. (LAUGHS)
-(CROWD CHEERING)

448
00:34:29.942 --> 00:34:31.109
MAN 2: Princess.

449
00:34:32.152 --> 00:34:33.486
MAN 3: Hi. Princess.

450
00:34:42.371 --> 00:34:44.873
(LIVELY CHATTER)

451
00:34:45.791 --> 00:34:47.125
KAYO: Profits have been good.

452
00:34:48.002 --> 00:34:50.087
After the disaster of the Republic.

453
00:34:50.170 --> 00:34:53.047
the Empire is finally lining
some pockets.

454
00:34:53.132 --> 00:34:55.843
There are still some issues
that we need to address.

455
00:34:56.427 --> 00:34:58.887
Slave labor. taxation
of the Outer Rim...

456
00:34:58.971 --> 00:35:01.473
I didn't come here to end slavery. Bail.

457
00:35:02.141 --> 00:35:03.851
I came to eat your food. (CHUCKLES)

458
00:35:04.643 --> 00:35:06.311
Save the bleeding heart for the Senate.

459
00:35:07.021 --> 00:35:08.939
A drink. Senator?

460
00:35:09.023 --> 00:35:10.065
(SIGHS)

461
00:35:10.524 --> 00:35:12.234
-Ah. Thank you.
-(ALIEN SPEAKING OTHER LANGUAGE)

462
00:35:12.318 --> 00:35:14.570
(C-3PO TRANSLATING IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

463
00:35:16.113 --> 00:35:17.197
Y-O: Your Highness.

464
00:35:17.489 --> 00:35:18.907
Oh. Thanks. Y-O.

465
00:35:18.991 --> 00:35:20.075
Y-O: My pleasure.

466
00:35:21.243 --> 00:35:22.452
(SCOFFS) You thank your droids?

467
00:35:23.078 --> 00:35:24.579
It's good manners.

468
00:35:24.663 --> 00:35:25.664
You don't need manners

469
00:35:25.748 --> 00:35:27.583
when you're talking
to a lower life form.

470
00:35:27.666 --> 00:35:30.835
Then I guess I don't need manners
when I'm talking to you.

471
00:35:31.211 --> 00:35:32.212
(CHUCKLES)

472
00:35:33.130 --> 00:35:35.715
You know the difference
between you and me. cousin?

473
00:35:36.425 --> 00:35:37.426
I know things.

474
00:35:38.010 --> 00:35:40.595
My father says
they never let you leave this planet.

475
00:35:41.805 --> 00:35:43.515
They don't want anybody
to know about you

476
00:35:43.599 --> 00:35:45.392
because you're not one of us.

477
00:35:46.435 --> 00:35:47.936
You're not even a real Organa.

478
00:35:49.980 --> 00:35:51.106
(SCOFFS)

479
00:35:52.650 --> 00:35:54.068
You're scared of him.

480
00:35:55.277 --> 00:35:58.822
Your father. You want him to like you.
So you repeat what he says

481
00:35:58.906 --> 00:36:01.325
even though you don't really know
what it means.

482
00:36:02.201 --> 00:36:04.995
You think being like him
will make people frightened of you.

483
00:36:05.079 --> 00:36:07.748
but really. you're the one who's scared.

484
00:36:07.831 --> 00:36:10.583
You've never made one decision
for yourself in your entire life.

485
00:36:10.668 --> 00:36:12.378
and you never will.

486
00:36:13.212 --> 00:36:16.006
I may not have seen much. cousin.

487
00:36:17.174 --> 00:36:18.425
but I can see that.

488
00:36:24.932 --> 00:36:26.850
He was being horrible to everyone.

489
00:36:26.934 --> 00:36:28.060
He's your cousin.

490
00:36:28.143 --> 00:36:29.644
He's rude to droids.

491
00:36:29.728 --> 00:36:31.980
You have to rise above. Leia.

492
00:36:34.733 --> 00:36:36.067
You owe him an apology.

493
00:36:36.527 --> 00:36:39.488
I'd rather be digested by a jakobeast.

494
00:36:51.333 --> 00:36:54.627
BAIL: I wanted to live out
way past Kathou

495
00:36:54.712 --> 00:36:55.754
when I was your age.

496
00:36:56.714 --> 00:36:59.550
Chase purrgil. you know?

497
00:36:59.633 --> 00:37:01.134
I had a whole plan.

498
00:37:02.928 --> 00:37:03.929
What happened?

499
00:37:04.680 --> 00:37:05.764
I got older.

500
00:37:06.640 --> 00:37:08.683
Had to find some other adventures.

501
00:37:09.685 --> 00:37:11.436
Started chasing your mother instead.

502
00:37:14.231 --> 00:37:15.899
This is your future. Leia.

503
00:37:16.692 --> 00:37:19.695
In a few years. you'll be
off to university. then Junior Senate.

504
00:37:19.778 --> 00:37:20.779
LEIA: The Senate's boring.

505
00:37:20.863 --> 00:37:23.282
It's people in itchy clothes arguing.

506
00:37:23.365 --> 00:37:26.284
(LAUGHING) Well. it may seem so...

507
00:37:26.368 --> 00:37:27.619
I don't want to be a senator.

508
00:37:28.162 --> 00:37:30.831
It is why
you'll probably be one of the best.

509
00:37:32.040 --> 00:37:34.000
I'm not even a real Organa.

510
00:37:34.918 --> 00:37:35.919
What?

511
00:37:40.674 --> 00:37:41.675
Don't ever say that.

512
00:37:43.802 --> 00:37:44.969
You are our child.

513
00:37:46.388 --> 00:37:50.517
You are an Organa in every way.

514
00:37:52.644 --> 00:37:54.937
One day. this planet
will look to you. Leia.

515
00:37:57.191 --> 00:37:58.692
There are many ways to lead.

516
00:37:58.776 --> 00:38:01.028
You just have to find yours.

517
00:38:01.111 --> 00:38:03.780
Plus. imagine the look
on your cousin's face

518
00:38:03.864 --> 00:38:05.949
when you get to
boss him around for real.

519
00:38:06.700 --> 00:38:07.701
(BOTH LAUGH)

520
00:38:09.995 --> 00:38:11.079
But for now.

521
00:38:12.956 --> 00:38:14.040
we will...

522
00:38:15.834 --> 00:38:17.001
apologize.

523
00:38:17.961 --> 00:38:18.962
Yes. Father.

524
00:38:19.046 --> 00:38:20.047
Hmm.

525
00:38:24.968 --> 00:38:26.469
I'll wait for you downstairs.

526
00:38:28.096 --> 00:38:29.138
(LEIA SIGHS)

527
00:38:42.903 --> 00:38:43.987
Thank you.

528
00:38:44.571 --> 00:38:45.655
She's gone.

529
00:38:45.864 --> 00:38:48.074
I thought you said
you've really got through to her.

530
00:38:48.575 --> 00:38:49.742
You know what she's like.

531
00:38:49.827 --> 00:38:51.245
I know who she's like.

532
00:38:51.995 --> 00:38:53.162
Send a unit.

533
00:38:53.247 --> 00:38:54.248
She can't be far.

534
00:39:01.672 --> 00:39:03.298
VECT: Hello. Princess.

535
00:39:05.509 --> 00:39:06.676
Why are you here?

536
00:39:07.719 --> 00:39:08.803
Just waiting.

537
00:39:09.263 --> 00:39:10.597
For what?

538
00:39:11.265 --> 00:39:12.599
For you.

539
00:39:12.975 --> 00:39:14.059
(GASPS)

540
00:39:15.936 --> 00:39:18.063
(LEIA PANTING)

541
00:39:24.236 --> 00:39:26.446
(ALL PANTING)

542
00:39:32.327 --> 00:39:33.328
(GRUNTING)

543
00:39:36.456 --> 00:39:37.498
(GRUNTS)

544
00:39:38.166 --> 00:39:39.417
(SHOUTING)

545
00:39:48.260 --> 00:39:49.302
(GROANS)

546
00:39:53.599 --> 00:39:54.683
LEIA: Help!

547
00:39:56.143 --> 00:39:57.227
Help!

548
00:39:57.311 --> 00:39:58.562
(PANTING)

549
00:39:58.645 --> 00:40:00.229
Help! Help me. please!

550
00:40:00.814 --> 00:40:01.898
(GROANS)

551
00:40:02.608 --> 00:40:04.818
(PANTING)

552
00:40:12.159 --> 00:40:15.328
(DEVICE BEEPING)

553
00:40:39.728 --> 00:40:41.312
We don't know who it was.

554
00:40:41.396 --> 00:40:43.022
No ransom. no leads.

555
00:40:44.358 --> 00:40:48.487
Whoever they are.
they knew where she would be. They...

556
00:40:49.196 --> 00:40:50.280
They were waiting.

557
00:40:50.364 --> 00:40:51.365
(CLEARS THROAT)

558
00:40:51.657 --> 00:40:53.575
She needs you. Obi-Wan.

559
00:40:54.618 --> 00:40:56.119
We can't trust anyone else.

560
00:40:58.288 --> 00:40:59.706
What about the Senate?

561
00:41:00.207 --> 00:41:01.958
BAIL: We cannot let this become public.

562
00:41:02.626 --> 00:41:04.377
It would draw too much attention.

563
00:41:05.212 --> 00:41:08.131
Well. your guard then?
Or a bounty hunter?

564
00:41:08.215 --> 00:41:12.302
Only you know how important
she really is. Obi-Wan.

565
00:41:12.386 --> 00:41:13.970
If Leia is discovered...

566
00:41:14.054 --> 00:41:15.638
I can't leave here. Bail.

567
00:41:16.848 --> 00:41:18.015
My duty is to the boy...

568
00:41:18.100 --> 00:41:20.018
What about your duty to his sister?

569
00:41:21.853 --> 00:41:23.688
She's as important as he is.

570
00:41:26.066 --> 00:41:27.442
(SIGHS)

571
00:41:29.903 --> 00:41:31.404
It's been ten years.

572
00:41:35.117 --> 00:41:36.535
I'm not who I used to be.

573
00:41:42.666 --> 00:41:43.750
Find someone else.

574
00:41:45.377 --> 00:41:46.544
She'll be better off.

575
00:41:47.879 --> 00:41:49.797
(WHOOSHING)

576
00:41:50.298 --> 00:41:52.758
LEIA: (GRUNTING) Let go of me!

577
00:41:52.843 --> 00:41:54.302
-Let go!
-Shut her up.

578
00:41:55.012 --> 00:41:57.347
(MERCENARY AND LEIA GRUNTING)

579
00:41:59.474 --> 00:42:03.974
(MERCENARY LAUGHING MANIACALLY)

580
00:42:06.023 --> 00:42:08.233
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)
(WORKERS CHATTERING)

581
00:42:29.379 --> 00:42:32.382
(CROWD GASPING. MURMURING)

582
00:43:00.702 --> 00:43:02.453
(MAN SOBBING)

583
00:43:13.465 --> 00:43:15.675
(WHIRRING)

584
00:43:39.866 --> 00:43:41.450
BAIL: She's headed for Daiyu.

585
00:43:43.620 --> 00:43:45.371
You should not have come.

586
00:43:46.331 --> 00:43:48.708
They hid their signature
behind a freight transport.

587
00:43:48.792 --> 00:43:50.627
The ship is on its way there now.

588
00:43:51.378 --> 00:43:52.420
I can't.

589
00:43:52.504 --> 00:43:54.255
She's my daughter. Obi-Wan.

590
00:43:54.339 --> 00:43:55.506
I told you...

591
00:43:56.591 --> 00:43:58.050
I'm not the man you remember.

592
00:43:58.135 --> 00:43:59.469
You're going to have to be!

593
00:43:59.553 --> 00:44:00.679
I can't leave the boy.

594
00:44:00.762 --> 00:44:02.680
This isn't about the boy.
and you know it!

595
00:44:03.807 --> 00:44:05.767
You've made mistakes. We all did.

596
00:44:05.851 --> 00:44:07.102
It's the past.

597
00:44:08.061 --> 00:44:09.562
Move on. Be done with it.

598
00:44:10.605 --> 00:44:12.273
You couldn't save Anakin.

599
00:44:14.234 --> 00:44:15.568
but you can save her.

600
00:44:18.196 --> 00:44:19.447
And what if I can't?

601
00:44:21.825 --> 00:44:24.744
There is no one
I trust more with my child than you.

602
00:44:26.621 --> 00:44:29.332
Please. old friend.

603
00:44:31.084 --> 00:44:32.168
For her.

604
00:44:33.545 --> 00:44:34.796
One last fight.

605
00:44:41.261 --> 00:44:42.637
(WHOOSHING)

606
00:44:44.514 --> 00:44:47.600
Come on. Lola. Come on.

607
00:44:49.728 --> 00:44:51.604
(LOLA ACTIVATES)

608
00:44:54.441 --> 00:44:57.402
(LOLA CHIRPING)

609
00:44:57.694 --> 00:44:59.570
(SHUSHING)

610
00:45:01.323 --> 00:45:02.824
Can you untie me?

611
00:45:08.038 --> 00:45:09.581
(DOOR OPENS)

612
00:45:11.166 --> 00:45:12.876
I'm not afraid of you.

613
00:45:13.126 --> 00:45:14.168
(SCOFFS)

614
00:45:14.961 --> 00:45:16.128
Give it time.

615
00:45:17.505 --> 00:45:19.590
(CHIRPING)

616
00:45:22.010 --> 00:45:23.136
Lola!

617
00:45:23.220 --> 00:45:24.429
(LOLA DEACTIVATES)

618
00:45:24.512 --> 00:45:26.805
My father will rescue me!

619
00:45:26.890 --> 00:45:28.850
He'll send a whole army!

620
00:45:29.434 --> 00:45:31.269
No one's coming for you.

621
00:45:38.068 --> 00:45:40.278
(DOOR CLOSING)

622
00:45:52.832 --> 00:45:54.750
(EOPIE GRUNTING)

623
00:46:25.407 --> 00:46:27.158
(LEIA GRUNTING)

624
00:46:28.410 --> 00:46:29.661
This is a bad idea.

625
00:46:30.412 --> 00:46:31.496
Kidnapping kids...

626
00:46:33.123 --> 00:46:34.290
you think it's gonna work?

627
00:46:34.874 --> 00:46:36.292
Just get this over with.

628
00:46:39.879 --> 00:46:40.921
(SYSTEM BEEPS)

629
00:47:17.167 --> 00:47:18.501
You sure he's gonna come?

630
00:47:19.377 --> 00:47:21.545
REVA: He fought beside her father
during the war.

631
00:47:22.505 --> 00:47:23.589
He'll come.

632
00:47:24.591 --> 00:47:26.092
He won't be able to help it.

633
00:47:27.302 --> 00:47:29.554
The Jedi will hunt himself.

634
00:47:32.349 --> 00:47:35.352
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
IN OTHER LANGUAGE ON PA)

635
00:47:56.790 --> 00:47:58.249
Well?

636
00:47:58.333 --> 00:47:59.500
You coming or not?

637
00:48:36.538 --> 00:48:38.581
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
